Gameplay and Rules of Teen Patti Master Purana
Basic Rules of Teen Patti
Teen Patti, often called the “Indian Poker,” is a fun and simple card game to play! It starts with each player receiving three cards face-down. The game is played with 3 to 6 players, and the objective is to have the best hand or make everyone else fold. The game ranking is similar to poker, where a Trio (three cards of the same rank) is the highest, followed by Straight Flush, Straight, Color, Pair, and High Card. So, if you’ve played a bit of poker, you’re already on the right track!
